Former Mamelodi Sundowns attacker Percy Tau is endearing himself to the fans of his new club Belgian side Royale Union Saint-Gilloise after he scored a cheeky goal in their 3-0 over City Pirates during the Croky Cup at the Joseph Marien Stadium at the weekend. Saint-Gilloise comfortably won the match 3-0 against third division outfit City Pirates in Belgium's Croky Cup. The 24-year old Tau, who is expected be part of Bafana Bafanaâ€™s squad to face Libya in the crucial Afcon qualifier next month, scored the third goal on his full debut late in the in the game against the third division outfit. Tau is spending the current campaign on a season-long loan with Saint-Gilloise from Brighton and Hove Albion in the English Premiership.